PROJECT
Retail Sales & Inventory Intelligence System (SQL-Based Project)

1. PROJECT OBJECTIVE
Build a pure database solution that:
Stores and manages retail data
Generates business reports using SQL
Performs analytics directly from the database
Simulates real-world operations using queries, procedures, and triggers

2. PROJECT APPROACH (NO WEB APP)
You will use:
MySQL / SQL Server
SQL Queries
Views
Stored Procedures
Triggers
Functions
Reports (via SQL)

3. DATABASE MODULE BREAKDOWN
A. SALES DOMAIN
customers
orders
order_items
staffs
stores
B. PRODUCTION DOMAIN
products
brands
categories
stocks

4. CORE BUSINESS OPERATIONS (SQL-ONLY)

OPERATION 1: Add New Customer
INSERT INTO customers (first_name, last_name, phone, email, city, state)
VALUES ('Ravi', 'Kumar', '9999999999', 'ravi@email.com', 'Hyderabad', 'Telangana');


OPERATION 2: Create Order
INSERT INTO orders (customer_id, order_status, order_date, store_id, staff_id)
VALUES (1, 1, GETDATE(), 1, 2);


OPERATION 3: Add Order Items
INSERT INTO order_items (order_id, item_id, product_id, quantity, list_price, discount)
VALUES (1, 1, 101, 2, 5000, 0.1);


OPERATION 4: Update Stock (Manual Simulation)
UPDATE stocks
SET quantity = quantity - 2
WHERE product_id = 101 AND store_id = 1;


5. AUTOMATION USING TRIGGERS
Auto-Reduce Stock on Order
CREATE TRIGGER trg_reduce_stock
ON order_items
AFTER INSERT
AS
BEGIN
    UPDATE s
    SET s.quantity = s.quantity - i.quantity
    FROM stocks s
    JOIN inserted i ON s.product_id = i.product_id;
END;


6. STORED PROCEDURES (REAL BUSINESS LOGIC)

Procedure: Place Order
CREATE PROCEDURE PlaceOrder
    @customer_id INT,
    @store_id INT,
    @staff_id INT
AS
BEGIN
    INSERT INTO orders (customer_id, order_status, order_date, store_id, staff_id)
    VALUES (@customer_id, 1, GETDATE(), @store_id, @staff_id);
END;


Procedure: Add Order Item
CREATE PROCEDURE AddOrderItem
    @order_id INT,
    @product_id INT,
    @quantity INT
AS
BEGIN
    DECLARE @price DECIMAL(10,2);

    SELECT @price = list_price FROM products WHERE product_id = @product_id;

    INSERT INTO order_items (order_id, item_id, product_id, quantity, list_price, discount)
    VALUES (@order_id, 1, @product_id, @quantity, @price, 0);
END;


7. VIEWS (BUSINESS REPORTS)

View: Customer Order Summary
CREATE VIEW customer_summary AS
SELECT c.customer_id, c.first_name, COUNT(o.order_id) AS total_orders
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.first_name;


View: Product Sales Summary
CREATE VIEW product_sales AS
SELECT p.product_name, SUM(oi.quantity) AS total_sold
FROM products p
JOIN order_items oi ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
GROUP BY p.product_name;


8. ANALYTICS QUERIES (CORE OF PROJECT)

1. Total Revenue
SELECT SUM(quantity * list_price * (1 - discount)) AS revenue
FROM order_items;


2. Top 5 Products
SELECT TOP 5 p.product_name, SUM(oi.quantity) AS total_sales
FROM products p
JOIN order_items oi ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
GROUP BY p.product_name
ORDER BY total_sales DESC;


3. Sales by Store
SELECT s.store_name, SUM(oi.quantity * oi.list_price) AS sales
FROM stores s
JOIN orders o ON s.store_id = o.store_id
JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id
GROUP BY s.store_name;


4. Monthly Sales
SELECT MONTH(order_date) AS month, SUM(oi.quantity * oi.list_price) AS revenue
FROM orders o
JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id
GROUP BY MONTH(order_date);


5. Low Stock Report
SELECT p.product_name, s.quantity
FROM stocks s
JOIN products p ON s.product_id = p.product_id
WHERE s.quantity < 5;


9. ADVANCED SQL FEATURES

1. Ranking (Top Staff)
SELECT staff_id,
       COUNT(order_id) AS total_orders,
       RANK() OVER (ORDER BY COUNT(order_id) DESC) AS rank_position
FROM orders
GROUP BY staff_id;


2. Running Total
SELECT order_date,
       SUM(quantity * list_price) OVER (ORDER BY order_date) AS running_total
FROM orders o
JOIN order_items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id;


